1. Which of the following questions can you ask to learn about your manager's motivations?
Solution : B. What do you hope to achieve in the coming year?

2. If your manager struggles with prioritizing projects, what is one way that you can help?
Solution : D. Keep your manager informed about deadlines as they approach

3. You're starting a new role and want clarity on what your manager expects for communication. What can you ask?
Solution : C. Is there a type of communication style that you prefer?

4. Your manager prefers to receive a broad outlook on your projects and day-to-day work. What can you do to keep your manager updated?
Solution : B. Write a weekly email with a brief synopsis of your progress and next steps
